Using the Cauchy-Schwarz inequality, we can write following
\begin{eqnarray*}
|B^{(p_{1},q_{1}),(p_{2},q_{2})}_{n,m}\left(f;x,y\right)-f(x,y)|&{\leqslant}&\parallel f^{'}_{x}\parallel_{C([0,1]^{2})}\{B^{(p_{1},q_{1}),(p_{2},q_{2})}_{n,m}\left((t-x)^{2};x,y\right)\}^{1/2}\{B^{(p_{1},q_{1}),(p_{2},q_{2})}_{n,m}\left(1;x,y\right)\}^{1/2}\\
&&+\parallel
f^{'}_{y}\parallel_{C([0,1]^{2})}\{B^{(p_{1},q_{1}),(p_{2},q_{2})}_{n,m}\left((s-y)^{2};x,y\right)\}^{1/2}\{B^{(p_{1},q_{1}),(p_{2},q_{2})}_{n,m}\left(1;x,y\right)\}^{1/2}.
\end{eqnarray*}
Form \eqref{moment1} and \eqref{moment2}, we get desired the result.
